We also explored an alternative to summarizing the joint distribution
of log R ratios.  At each marker, we subtract the estimated log R
ratio of the offspring from the offspring's mother and father.  Both
minimum and maximum distances are retained.  To identify \denovo{}
deletions, we smoothed the minimum distance as a function of physical
position using circular binary segmentation (CBS; \cite{}). Parameter
settings used for CBS are provided in Section \ref{sec:sm}.  We use an
\adhoc{} approach for calling \denovo{} deletions that is a function
of the amplitidue of the minimum distance and coverage. Figure X plots
the minimum segment mean required for calling a deletion versus
coverage. Implicitly, the uncertainty of the segment mean is larger
for regions with less coverage and less for regions with high
coverage.

