\section{Results}

\paragraph{Obtaining a set of high-quality samples for CNV analysis}
The noise of BeadStudio log R ratios was strongly influenced by WGA,
and this affected subsequent inference via a HMM.  Trio were excluded
from subsequent analyses if any member in the trio had DNA that was
WGA or if the MAD of the log R ratios exceeded 0.3.  We also assessed
whether the number of \denovo{} events was associated with
site. Supplementary Figure X shows that samples from site 23 tended to
have higher \denovo{} call rates than other sites.  Further analysis
revealed that the high call rates were primarily on two of the plates
from site 23. Did the samples on these plates have abnormally high log
R ratios?

