\paragraph{High frequency \denovo{} CNV} The joint HMM provides a
likelihood based approach for inferring the genomic start and stop
coordinates of the \denovo{} events.  Figure X plots genomic position
on the x-axis versus the offspring index.  The shaded rectanges
indicate inferred \denovo{} events and the color codes indicate
whether the \denovo{} event corresponds to a copy number deletion or
duplication in the offspring. Vertical stripes in this figure
correspond to sites for which there appears to be a frequent
recombination event from parent to offspring that results in loss or
gain of DNA copy number in the offspring.  There are also many
horizontal stripes.  Horizontal stripes likely represent technological
artifact.  (TODO: Ordering the offsrping by (site, dna source, MAD)
